5|$|Black <b>Hebrew</b> Israelites (also called Black Hebrews, African <b>Hebrew</b> Israelites, and <b>Hebrew</b> Israelites) are {{groups of}} African Americans {{who believe that}} they are {{descendants}} of the ancient Israelites. Black Hebrews adhere in varying degrees to the religious beliefs and practices of both Christianity and Judaism. They are not recognized as Jews by the greater Jewish community. Many choose to identify themselves as <b>Hebrew</b> Israelites or Black Hebrews rather than Jews in order to indicate their claimed historic connections.|$|E
