5|$|The archeological {{record for}} the {{prehistory}} of Biblical <b>Hebrew</b> is far more complete than the record of Biblical <b>Hebrew</b> itself. Early Northwest Semitic (ENWS) materials are attested from 2350BCE to 1200BCE, {{the end of the}} Bronze Age. The Northwest Semitic languages, including <b>Hebrew,</b> differentiated noticeably during the Iron Age (1200–540BCE), although in its earliest stages Biblical <b>Hebrew</b> was not highly differentiated from Ugaritic and the Canaanite of the Amarna letters.|$|E
